<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-04T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-04T13:00:00-05:00" n="652" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d652">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">860C.001 Moscicki, Ignacy/28:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gunther</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-04T20:00:00+02:00">October 4, 1939—8
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>306. My 290, October 1, 5 p.m. Mr. Michel Moscicki has again called
                                and states that he found his father in very good shape. He said that
                                the Rumanian Prime Minister<note n="58" xml:id="d652fn58">General
                                    Argetoianu.</note> had especially requested that no <pb facs="0704" n="696" xml:id="pg_696"/> mention be made of the
                                ex-President’s idea of possibly going eventually to the United
                                States. He confirmed my understanding that he would go first to
                                Switzerland and said that all arrangements had now been made. As you
                                may know ex-President Moscicki acquired Swiss nationality when there
                                as a young man and has never renounced it.</p>
                            <p>Above not repeated to Paris.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>